M/S. Y. L. AGARWALLA & ORS V. COMMISSIONER OF INCOME-TAX, CENTRAL, CALCUTTA [1978] INSC 116; AIR 1978 SC 1412; 1978 (3) SCR 1059; 1978 (3) SCC 426 (27 July 1978)

 TULZAPURKAR, V.D.
 TULZAPURKAR, V.D.
 BHAGWATI, P.N.
 
CITATION: 1978 AIR 1412 1978 SCR (3)1059 1978 SCC (3) 426 
ACT:
 Hindu Undivided Family Firm-Karta having 36% shares as one of the partners of partnership firm and after his death his widow and three daughters declined to continue in the partnership, but his three minor sons were admitted into partnership with 14% shares each under a new deed--Clause 6 of the new deed ensure to the firm the continued use of the capital of Hindu Undivided Family standing in the account of the minors' late father, free of interest--whether the share income of three minor sons front the partnership firm liable to be assessed as the income of Hindu Undivided Family ? 
